parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to shudder, jerk, or hesitate while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: especially when accelerating or decelerating; the transmission slips or fails to engage; the vehicle stalls or loses power; the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission judder or shudder can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to a loss of acceleration, hesitation, or stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission judders or shudders while driving
especially when accelerating or decelerating; the vehicle hesitates or loses power; the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure to engage can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to a loss of acceleration, hesitation, or stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or fails to engage; the vehicle hesitates or loses power; the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light remains on or flashes even when an adult or child is sitting in the passenger seat
the airbag warning light is illuminated
and the system fails to detect an occupant in the passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Rusting or corrosion of the subframe
snapping or breaking of the subframe
pulling to one side while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause distraction, loss of control, and injuries.
The failure of the transmission can cause loss of power, stalling, and accidents.
symptoms: Stuttering or hesitation when accelerating or decelerating

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas pedal can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and causing accidents.
The failure of the sun visor can cause obstruction of the driver's view, distraction, and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
The failure of the door handles can cause difficulty in exiting the vehicle in an emergency, increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities.

symptoms: Rear tailgate not opening or malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan can cause overheating, engine damage, and accidents.
